title: New minister weighing Indon beef imports
text:
Wed, Aug 19, 2015, 6:02 PM AEST - Australia Markets closed New minister weighing Indon beef imports AAP – 16 minutes ago Print 
Indonesia's new trade minister is ready to flood the markets with imported beef to bring down the price, but only if it's necessary. 
Tom Lembong met President Joko Widodo on Wednesday to discuss the beef price spike that resulted after his predecessor slashed permits for Australian live cattle imports. 
Mr Lembong says he'll watch the market before issuing permits for between 200,000 and 300,000 head of cattle in the last quarter of the year, telling reporters: "If the price goes down by itself, why must we import? @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Reject Shop says profit growth will return AAP
